HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 57
BY REPRESENTATIVE LACOMBE
A RESOLUTION
To commend Jensen LeBlanc for being named a National Champion for Children's Miracle
Network.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Jensen LeBlanc for promoting the
importance of children's healthcare and to commend him for being named a National
Champion for Children's Miracle Network; and
WHEREAS, Jensen LeBlanc is a vibrant and resilient eleven-year-old resident of
Addis, Louisiana, who has been a patient of Our Lady of the Lake (OLOL) Children's
Hospital since he was seven months old; and
WHEREAS, Jensen is a powerful advocate for pediatric patients, and his heartfelt
efforts have brought awareness to the importance of children's healthcare and the life-
changing impact that OLOL Children's Hospital has made in the greater Baton Rouge area;
and
WHEREAS, through his role as the Children's Miracle Network Champion for
OLOL Children's Hospital, Jensen serves as the main patient ambassador and has become
a local celebrity; he attends community events and corporate partner meetings and shares his
healthcare story and OLOL's impact to promote community and corporate fundraising for
the hospital; and
WHEREAS, Jensen has inspired countless individuals through his outreach efforts
and contributed significantly to increased community involvement and fundraising support
for the hospital's programs and services; and
WHEREAS, Addis Mayor David Toups presented Jensen with a key to the city in
recognition of his remarkable leadership and sense of civic responsibility; and
