HR NO. 57 ENROLLED
WHEREAS, Jensen serves as a 2026 National Champion for Children's Miracle
Network; he is one of nineteen patients across the United States who represent all one
hundred seventy local Children's Miracle Network hospitals in the country; and
WHEREAS, Jensen LeBlanc is a truly inspiring young man who is most deserving
of the highest recognition for his work to create positive change in the state and across the
country.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Jensen LeBlanc for being named a National
Champion for Children's Miracle Network; does hereby express enduring appreciation for
his exceptional sense of civic duty in advocating for the importance of children's healthcare;
and does hereby extend sincere wishes that he remain prosperous in all of his endeavors.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
